titles.title: A bill to extend the existing suspension of duty on metal oxide varistors.

action.text: Sponsor introductory remarks on measure. (CR S1890)
Read twice and referred to the Committee on Finance.

bill.summary: 2/18/1993--Introduced. Amends the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to extend, through December 31, 1997, the suspension of duty on metal oxide varistors weighing less than 2.5 kilograms.
